<TITLE> Cabinet backs Climate Change Trust Policy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, February 2 (bdnews24.com)The cabinet Monday approved in principal the Climate Change Trust Policy, but sent back a proposal on a trade investment pact with India for further scrutiny. "The Climate Change Trust Policy has been approved on principle. But the cabinet stressed the need for proper utilisation of the fund to ensure people's welfare," the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad told reporters after the cabinet meeting. "A fund administration committee headed by the prime minister's financial adviser has been formed for proper operation of the Trust." Other members of the committee are the civil aviation and tourism minister, state ministers for forest and environment, foreign affairs and housing and public works, and the concerned secretaries. A strategy and action plan committee headed by the planning minister was also formed at the meeting, its membership to comprise the agriculture minister, food minister and fund administration committee members. The cabinet meeting also mulled a Bangladesh-India Capital Investment Development Protection Agreement, the PM's press secretary said. The proposal was sent back for further scrutiny, in light of similar treaties, before placing before the cabinet again. bdnews2
